Running the MongoDB server:
=>brew services start mongodb-community@4.4

Connect to your database:
To connect to your MongoDB databases, in a NEW terminal (after installing, you must open a new terminal), type...
=>mongo

Now you should see the terminal cursor become a single arrow and blinking underscore. We're in!

Stopping the MongoDB server:
To stop mongod running as a macOS service, use the following command as needed:
=>brew services stop mongodb-community@4.4

Database Type: SQL | Mongo
Database : Schema | Database (db)
Collection of related records: Tables | Collections
Each one record in the collection of records: Row / Record | Document
